1
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:10,367
<i>We've gone through so many
rounds,</i>

2
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,000
<i>but there's still no improvement
in her condition.</i>

3
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:14,233
<i> She's getting weaker.</i>

4
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:16,167
<i>Mrs. Torrecampo,
we're doing our best.</i>

5
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:17,400
<i> I just miss Jas.</i>

6
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:18,400
<i> You're not gonna lose her.</i>

7
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:19,900
<i>Even if she's sick,
she's strong.</i>

8
00:00:20,033 --> 00:00:21,133
<i> She's a fighter.</i>

9
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:23,633
<i>I can't stand watching
my daughter suffer anymore.</i>

10
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,367
<i> Let's go home.</i>

11
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,433
<i>You put my grandchild's life
in danger!</i>

12
00:00:28,567 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>You didn't just disrespect
your husband, but us, too.</i>

13
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:32,300
<i> Honestly, Marj,</i>

14
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:35,100
<i>you're the one making our
daughter's condition worse.</i>

15
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:37,800
<i>Just like how you killed
our relationship!</i>

16
00:00:37,933 --> 00:00:39,400
<i> I'm so exhausted, Manang.</i>

17
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:40,500
<i> I don't even know</i>

18
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:42,333
<i>if what I'm doing
is still the right thing.</i>

19
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:43,967
<i>I'll sleep in the guest room
for now.</i>

20
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:45,900
<i> Please, can we talk, Paolo?</i>

21
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:47,300
<i> I can't talk right now.</i>

22
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,333
You called for me, Ma'am Thea?

23
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:12,733
You have siblings back
in the province, right?

24
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:14,333
And you're the one putting
them through school?

25
00:01:15,567 --> 00:01:16,800
Yes, Ma'am.

26
00:01:16,933 --> 00:01:18,433
Why do you ask?

27
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:30,433
Ma'am, what's this for?

28
00:01:30,567 --> 00:01:31,967
Why are you giving me money?

29
00:01:34,133 --> 00:01:39,467
Out of all the maids here,
you're my favorite, Cheche.

30
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,300
I really think we'll get along.

31
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:45,567
That's why I'm giving you that.

32
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:48,600
And in return...

33
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:50,400
I have something
I need you to do.

34
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:53,267
What is it, Ma'am?

35
00:01:56,967 --> 00:02:00,333
I want you to be my eyes
and ears in this house.

36
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,900
Spy on Marj.

37
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:05,200
I want to know her every move.

38
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:08,367
And do everything you can
to keep her and Paolo

39
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:09,600
from making up.

40
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:14,167
But why, Ma'am Thea?

41
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:17,400
No more questions.

42
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:19,433
Just do what I said.

43
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:22,667
And I promise,
I'll give you more.

44
00:02:23,633 --> 00:02:27,833
Whatever Marj does,
I want you to sabotage it.

45
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:29,667
Got it?

46
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:35,467
You don't seem interested.

47
00:02:43,367 --> 00:02:44,267
I will, Ma'am.

48
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,233
<i> We're sorry.</i>

49
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:54,233
<i>The number you have reached
is not in service.</i>

50
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:12,700
Ma'am Marj, I can do that
for you.

51
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:13,767
Thanks, Cheche.

52
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:15,767
But I want to do this myself.

53
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,300
It's a peace offering for Paolo.

54
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:23,600
This is good enough.

55
00:04:25,367 --> 00:04:27,000
Che, when the broth gets low,

56
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:30,700
just turn it off and leave it
covered, okay?

57
00:04:30,867 --> 00:04:32,733
I'll just give Jasmine
her medicine.

58
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:33,867
Okay?

59
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,233
Thank you.

60
00:05:07,767 --> 00:05:08,533
Ma'am.

61
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:12,533
So?

62
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:14,133
Did you do what I told you?

63
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:19,000
Good job.

64
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:21,233
Very good.

65
00:05:26,767 --> 00:05:27,667
What is this?

66
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,133
Why is it so salty?

67
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:31,967
Are you trying to kill me?

68
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,000
What the heck!

69
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:36,833
Don't get mad.

70
00:05:36,967 --> 00:05:39,367
I made that juice myself.

71
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,267
I was hoping you'd like it.

72
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,233
After all, it's a dose
of your own medicine.

73
00:05:46,033 --> 00:05:48,400
Ma'am Thea, I'm sorry.

74
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:52,367
I really couldn't do
what you asked,

75
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:57,767
so I told Ma'am Marj everything.

76
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,800
I'm sorry...

77
00:05:59,933 --> 00:06:02,867
How dare you go against me?

78
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,600
You're useless!

79
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:05,967
That's enough!

80
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,167
Thea, stop it!

81
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,333
Go back to the kitchen.

82
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,033
I'll handle this.

83
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:11,300
What's your problem, huh?

84
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:14,267
Why did you order Cheche
to sabotage me?

85
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:16,300
Do you really want my husband
and me to fight?

86
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:17,833
What are you trying to achieve?

87
00:06:17,967 --> 00:06:21,400
I got pissed at you
after our last argument.

88
00:06:21,533 --> 00:06:22,967
I was so annoyed,

89
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:26,467
I asked Cheche to watch
your every move.

90
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:29,300
To report all your mistakes
to me.

91
00:06:29,433 --> 00:06:32,767
But I never told her
to sabotage you, okay?

92
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,500
I'm sure she just made that up.

93
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:35,667
Wow.

94
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,900
You're unbelievable.

95
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:41,067
You've been caught red-handed,
and you're still denying it?

96
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:43,900
I don't care if you
don't believe me, Marj.

97
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:46,600
If you want to tell everyone,
go ahead.

98
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:48,300
Be my guest.

99
00:06:48,433 --> 00:06:51,667
Who do you think
they'll believe?

100
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:55,567
Me or someone who's just a maid?

101
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:56,933
Don't worry.

102
00:06:57,067 --> 00:07:00,167
I'm not planning to broadcast
everything you've done.

103
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:03,667
I know how good you
are at twisting things.

104
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:06,667
And I don't want to add
more chaos to this house.

105
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,567
But listen carefully.

106
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,300
You're smart, right?

107
00:07:10,433 --> 00:07:12,800
The next time you order Cheche
around

108
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:16,733
or try to sabotage my marriage
to Paolo,

109
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:19,700
I won't just make you drink
juice.

110
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:22,700
I'll make you eat every piece
of garbage outside

111
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:25,167
since that's exactly
what your attitude is.

112
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,500
Look at the spaces, Ma'am.

113
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:42,067
They're big, right?

114
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,700
This brochure is yours
so can have youtr copy.

115
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:45,767
Excuse me.

116
00:07:52,133 --> 00:07:54,300
Paolo, what's wrong with you?

117
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:55,900
You've been out of it
this whole time!

118
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:00,833
If your energy stays this low,

119
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:04,100
no clients are going to be
interested in this property.

120
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:07,500
Sorry.

121
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:11,200
Marj and I had a big fight.

122
00:08:12,667 --> 00:08:15,600
I just can't get it
out of my head.

123
00:08:15,733 --> 00:08:17,233
Try harder.

124
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:22,933
Or clients might go running
to that arrogant guy.

125
00:08:26,367 --> 00:08:27,867
Careful, Jasmine.

126
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:30,267
Xander?

127
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:36,900
Easy.

128
00:08:37,033 --> 00:08:38,900
You're here.

129
00:08:39,033 --> 00:08:41,967
Why didn't you even message me
that you were coming?

130
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:45,500
Ash texted me, so I came right
away to welcome you back.

131
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:49,167
Surprise, cuz.

132
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,667
Thank you.

133
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,300
Ash, I'll take it from here.

134
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:55,700
Sure.

135
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,000
See you guys.

136
00:09:02,067 --> 00:09:04,600
You know what's funny?

137
00:09:04,733 --> 00:09:07,533
They think just because
their properties carry

138
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:08,967
the Torrecampo name,

139
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:11,533
they'll sell easily.

140
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:15,700
But they miscalculated
market demand.

141
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:17,767
And their prices
are way too high.

142
00:09:19,467 --> 00:09:21,767
Do they really think rich
families will pay anything

143
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,567
for luxury?

144
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:24,867
I don't think so.

145
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:28,700
Well, I guess we all just
figure out our own way

146
00:09:28,867 --> 00:09:31,400
to move these properties.

147
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,833
We can't rely on management.

148
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
They can't even fix their
own family,

149
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:39,933
what more this company.

150
00:09:40,067 --> 00:09:42,333
Paolo, don't let it get in your
head.

151
00:09:42,467 --> 00:09:44,533
Shut your foul mouth!

152
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,100
Stop it! Paolo!

153
00:09:46,233 --> 00:09:47,000
Paolo!

154
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,233
Paolo, enough!

155
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:04,233
Let's go.

156
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:05,667
Let's get out of here.

157
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:09,767
Let's go!

158
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:17,033
Come on!

159
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:25,600
Give it to me.

160
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:27,033
Don't bother.

161
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:28,700
It's just a scratch.

162
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,500
Stop arguing.

163
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:32,467
We need to clean it
so it doesn't get infected.

164
00:10:35,433 --> 00:10:38,633
He really shouldn't
have said that.

165
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,333
Not in front of everyone.

166
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:43,767
He did it on purpose
to make me snap.

167
00:10:45,033 --> 00:10:48,067
He wants people to think
I'm an ineffective leader.

168
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:53,433
Paolo, I know you're
going through a lot.

169
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:57,367
But you can't keep
everything bottled up.

170
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:01,133
That's why you end up
exploding like that.

171
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:11,000
You don't always have to handle
everything alone.

172
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,000
I'm here.

173
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:17,500
If you need someone to talk to,
I'll listen.

174
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:20,667
I'm not like the others

175
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:24,433
who undermine whatever you think
is best for the company

176
00:11:24,567 --> 00:11:25,533
or in the family.

177
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:31,533
I'm glad you're different.

178
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,300
Sorry.

179
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:40,500
It's fine now.

180
00:11:41,067 --> 00:11:41,833
Thank you.

181
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,833
Honey, it's cold out here.

182
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:29,233
Here.

183
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:33,433
Go rest in your room.

184
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:35,467
You have an early
checkup tomorrow.

185
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:37,933
Okay, Mom.

186
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,367
There you are, Jasmine!

187
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:49,533
Sweetheart, this is Nurse Daisy,
okay?

188
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:52,967
Starting today, she'll
be taking care of you.

189
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:54,333
If anything unusual happens,

190
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:56,600
report it to Paolo and me,
all right?

191
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:57,833
Yolly, please go with them.

192
00:12:57,967 --> 00:12:59,100
Yes, Ma'am.

193
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:01,400
All right, sweetheart,
get some rest.

194
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,167
Mom, I appreciate
your concern...

195
00:13:18,300 --> 00:13:19,267
and that you hired a nurse.

196
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,567
But didn't we learn
our lesson before?

197
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:23,267
Back when Jas was a baby?

198
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:27,167
Her nurse ended up being
neglectful instead of helpful.

199
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,133
Marj, this is different.

200
00:13:28,267 --> 00:13:30,467
She's highly qualified.

201
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:33,900
I believe I can take care
of my child.

202
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:36,367
And Manang Yolly
has been helping, too.

203
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:37,667
Marj, relax.

204
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:40,800
I'm just trying to help you
put this house back in order.

205
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:43,367
Because when things
are chaotic at home,

206
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:46,467
everyone pays the price,
especially the child.

207
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,900
Just to be clear,

208
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:51,033
this is so Jasmine's healing
can have structure.

209
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:53,667
And so you can finally
focus on Paolo.

210
00:13:56,633 --> 00:14:01,533
As Jasmine's mother,
I hope you won't overstep me.

211
00:14:01,667 --> 00:14:04,433
Please let me make decisions
for...

212
00:14:04,567 --> 00:14:05,600
What do you even know?

213
00:14:06,733 --> 00:14:08,133
Weren't you the one
who took my granddaughter

214
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:10,833
to Hong Kong so doctors could
practice on her?

215
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:13,967
Mom, it wasn't like that.

216
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,333
That was a decision I made

217
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:16,700
because I didn't want
to reach a point

218
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,733
where I'd regret not doing
everything I could

219
00:14:18,867 --> 00:14:20,367
to save my child.

220
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,733
Hey, what's going on here?

221
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:24,067
There.

222
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:26,067
Talk to your wife.

223
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,500
I was just looking out
for Jasmine,

224
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:30,667
so I hired professional care.

225
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:33,367
And she's taking it
the wrong way.

226
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,667
I never said that.

227
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:40,367
I just wish she had consulted us
first before hiring a nurse.

228
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:42,067
Marj, I know.

229
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:45,133
Mom told me, and I support it.

230
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:46,833
She just wants to help.

231
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:50,900
What?

232
00:14:51,033 --> 00:14:54,533
You knew about this
and didn't tell me?

233
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:56,533
What is this?
Are you getting back at me?

234
00:14:56,667 --> 00:14:58,933
That's not the issue.

235
00:14:59,067 --> 00:14:59,933
Okay?

236
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:02,200
People are just doing what they
can to help.

237
00:15:02,367 --> 00:15:04,567
Jasmine needs support.

238
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:05,833
And after what happened,

239
00:15:05,967 --> 00:15:09,867
we need to limit the decisions
that you make on your own.

240
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,400
Paolo's right.

241
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:15,167
If you really love Jasmine,

242
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:17,833
then learn to listen to people
who know better

243
00:15:17,967 --> 00:15:20,667
instead of letting your emotions
control everything.

244
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:27,067
I know Jasmine's treatment
in Hong Kong didn't work.

245
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,300
But please don't do this to me.

246
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:33,200
Don't take away my right to make
decisions for my own child.

247
00:15:54,467 --> 00:16:02,400
None of this would've happened
if you hadn't interfered.

248
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:04,167
If you hadn't pushed Marj
to put Jasmine at risk.

249
00:16:09,767 --> 00:16:10,467
Me?

250
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:15,233
I'm still the one to blame
for everything?

251
00:16:15,367 --> 00:16:16,933
Yes.

252
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:18,500
We already know this, Edward.

253
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:21,967
From the very beginning,

254
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:24,367
all you've ever brought
into this family is trouble.

255
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,733
Is this really who we are now?

256
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:30,533
Ever since Jasmine and I
came back,

257
00:16:30,667 --> 00:16:34,467
it feels like I committed
some kind of crime.

258
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:37,067
And now, you've completely
shut me out of my own child?

259
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:40,200
So now you know how it feels.

260
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,667
That's exactly what you did
to me, remember?

261
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:46,467
You put our child in danger
even when I was against it.

262
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,833
You made that decision
on your own!

263
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:50,167
I did that for Jasmine!

264
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,067
Are you blind?

265
00:16:52,867 --> 00:16:54,667
Can't you see Paolo
has his faults too?

266
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:57,433
He makes bad decisions.

267
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:59,400
He ruins things.

268
00:16:59,533 --> 00:17:00,467
But no matter what he does,

269
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,067
in your eyes,
he's always the good one.

270
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:08,667
Yes.

271
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:13,133
Because even if you add up
all of Paolo's mistakes,

272
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:15,833
they still wouldn't
come close to yours.

273
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:20,233
He's the only son I can rely on.

274
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:23,133
The only one I'm proud of.

275
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:26,267
We just keep throwing
blame at each other!

276
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,567
This isn't how we're
supposed to be.

277
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:29,433
We're married.

278
00:17:29,567 --> 00:17:31,200
We're supposed to be a team.

279
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:34,233
Not hurting each other
like this.

280
00:17:34,367 --> 00:17:36,067
I don't need a team!

281
00:17:36,933 --> 00:17:39,367
What I need is a wife
who trusts me,

282
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,767
who listens to me.

283
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:42,600
Not someone who
keeps dismissing me!

284
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:44,600
That's what you want.

285
00:17:44,733 --> 00:17:46,267
Someone who just obeys you.

286
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,667
Someone you can control.

287
00:17:52,633 --> 00:17:53,567
You?

288
00:17:56,933 --> 00:17:58,967
You're always the one
who needs fixing.

289
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:02,700
Someone who always has excuses.

290
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:05,933
Who always has problems.

291
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:12,700
So no matter what I do,
it'll never be enough for you?

292
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:18,600
Finally, you get it.

293
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:24,233
I only let you move back in
because of my granddaughter.

294
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:30,400
If not for Ashley,
you wouldn't even be here.

295
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:35,233
Why would I care about you?

296
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:37,800
This isn't about control.

297
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:39,300
Oh really?

298
00:18:39,433 --> 00:18:42,500
Then why did you take away
my say in raising our child?

299
00:18:42,633 --> 00:18:44,700
Don't you really
trust me anymore?

300
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,500
What happened to you?

301
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:47,800
Even if you disappeared...

302
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:53,500
or if the people you owe money
to got rid of you,

303
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:56,967
I wouldn't care.

304
00:18:58,633 --> 00:19:00,033
I wouldn't lose anything.

305
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:05,933
It'd be a good riddance.

306
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:20,300
Where is the person who used
to be on my side in this house?

307
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:22,167
Where's the man I married?

308
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:23,867
And you...

309
00:19:26,267 --> 00:19:27,200
are you still the same person?

310
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,633
Are you still the woman
I married?

311
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:39,933
Hi.

312
00:19:40,067 --> 00:19:42,733
Daisy, please leave Jasmine
and me alone for a bit.

313
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:46,267
Thank you.

314
00:19:54,733 --> 00:19:55,967
How are you, sweetheart?

315
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,233
Are you two getting along?

316
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:01,367
She's okay, Mom.

317
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,833
That's good.

318
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,067
At least there's someone
here to take care of you,

319
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,133
whom they all trust.

320
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,533
Mom, don't say that.

321
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:12,500
No, don't worry.

322
00:20:16,033 --> 00:20:18,167
I'll still come by
whenever you need me.

323
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:21,233
I'll go with you
to your treatments,

324
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:24,400
your checkups, everything, dear.

325
00:20:24,533 --> 00:20:26,400
Why are you saying that, Mom?

326
00:20:26,533 --> 00:20:28,333
Where are you going?

327
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:30,333
Mom just needs to rest
for a while.

328
00:20:32,767 --> 00:20:35,400
But you're still sleeping here
at the house, right?

329
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:39,433
Not for now, sweetheart.

330
00:20:40,433 --> 00:20:43,133
I don't want the fights
between your dad and me

331
00:20:43,267 --> 00:20:45,067
to add more stress for you.

332
00:20:46,233 --> 00:20:47,333
I don't want you to see that...

333
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:49,100
or feel it.

334
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,667
I'll video call you every day.

335
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:57,500
I promise,
I'll still come visit.

336
00:20:58,367 --> 00:20:59,700
I'll check on you.

337
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,567
And I'm still your mom.

338
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:03,933
That's never going to change.

339
00:21:35,767 --> 00:21:36,667
What's this?

340
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:40,033
Are you really leaving?

341
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:43,267
You're just going to walk out
on Jasmine and me?

342
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:48,000
I know you'd never
abandon our child.

343
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:51,633
But that doesn't mean
I have to stay here.

344
00:21:53,733 --> 00:21:55,367
I'll be staying at my mom's
house for now.

345
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:00,367
Hey. You wanted to talk
last time, right?

346
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:03,400
Come on, let's talk now.

347
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:08,133
About what?

348
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:11,267
To fix things?

349
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:14,533
So you can prove
you're right again?

350
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:17,400
So you can control everything?

351
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:26,700
I don't have the energy
to argue with you anymore.

352
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:29,667
Especially when you treat this

353
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,733
like one of your
company problems.

354
00:22:33,133 --> 00:22:36,533
When everyone in this house
keeps making me feel

355
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:40,300
like I'm useless,
like I don't have a voice.

356
00:22:41,533 --> 00:22:42,533
I have no one on my side...

357
00:22:42,667 --> 00:22:44,533
no one to fight for Jasmine's
health with me...

358
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:49,300
or to fight for whether I still
have a place in this family...

359
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:51,467
and in your life.

360
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:34,533
So is this goodbye for good,
Marj?

361
00:23:34,667 --> 00:23:36,033
Or is this just another stunt

362
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:38,133
so Paolo will come running
after you?

363
00:23:38,267 --> 00:23:40,067
Because if it is...

364
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,700
it doesn't seem to be working.

365
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:45,100
Can you not do this right now?

366
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:46,533
I already have a lot on my mind.

367
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:49,800
I'm just saying.

368
00:23:49,933 --> 00:23:53,533
Once you start something,
you better follow through.

369
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:56,800
If I were you,
I wouldn't come back

370
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:58,933
the moment I walk out that door.

371
00:23:59,067 --> 00:24:01,167
Let's face it.

372
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:04,333
Your marriage to Paolo
is beyond repair.

373
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:08,133
And honestly,
Jasmine might be better off

374
00:24:08,267 --> 00:24:10,400
if you two just separate
for good.

375
00:24:10,533 --> 00:24:12,933
I'm leaving so I can think.

376
00:24:13,067 --> 00:24:16,400
That doesn't mean I'm giving up
on my marriage or my family.

377
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:18,733
Are you sure?

378
00:24:18,867 --> 00:24:21,400
Do you really think
Paolo wants you back?

379
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:24,833
You've been getting into
his head, haven't you?

380
00:24:24,967 --> 00:24:28,500
Are you the one pushing him
to hate me even more?

381
00:24:29,433 --> 00:24:31,000
Excuse me?

382
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:32,867
Don't jump to conclusions.

383
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:36,367
Your failure as a wife has
nothing to do with me.

384
00:24:39,867 --> 00:24:40,767
Move!

385
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:47,133
- Hey!
- That hurts!

386
00:24:47,267 --> 00:24:48,333
- Hey!
- Oh my God!

387
00:24:48,467 --> 00:24:50,800
What in heaven's name
are you doing, Marjorie?

388
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:53,000
Are you okay?

389
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:55,200
Mom...

390
00:24:55,333 --> 00:24:58,533
I was just trying to convince
Marj to stay.

391
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:03,100
I thought maybe she and Paolo
could still fix things.

392
00:25:03,267 --> 00:25:05,733
But she took it the wrong way.

393
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:10,133
Marjorie, if you're not going
to do anything good here,

394
00:25:10,267 --> 00:25:12,033
then maybe it's better
if you leave.

395
00:25:12,167 --> 00:25:13,800
Stop causing trouble.

396
00:25:15,033 --> 00:25:19,433
Mom, why do you always take
her side?

397
00:25:19,567 --> 00:25:22,167
You don't even know
the whole story.

398
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:26,133
Because Thea listens,
and she knows how to respect us.

399
00:25:26,267 --> 00:25:28,367
You don't.

400
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:31,333
Maybe you should open your eyes
for once

401
00:25:31,467 --> 00:25:34,733
and learn the difference
between respect and sucking up.

402
00:25:35,967 --> 00:25:37,700
Thea just acts nice.

403
00:25:37,833 --> 00:25:39,233
She's like candy.

404
00:25:39,367 --> 00:25:41,800
Sweet on the outside,
but wrapped in plastic.

405
00:25:48,167 --> 00:25:49,267
Are you okay?

406
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:00,567
I'm in.

407
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:01,400
Great.

408
00:26:01,533 --> 00:26:02,433
Great decision.

409
00:26:02,567 --> 00:26:04,300
What made you change your mind?

410
00:26:04,433 --> 00:26:05,200
My dad.

411
00:26:05,333 --> 00:26:06,833
He's never treated me
like family.

412
00:26:06,967 --> 00:26:09,200
In his eyes,
Paolo is still perfect,

413
00:26:09,367 --> 00:26:11,033
no matter what my brother does.

414
00:26:11,167 --> 00:26:13,200
And I want to prove to them that
his wrong.

415
00:26:13,333 --> 00:26:15,400
So the rumors are true.

416
00:26:15,533 --> 00:26:17,233
Your real wife...

417
00:26:17,367 --> 00:26:18,600
is this office.

418
00:26:18,733 --> 00:26:22,800
The problem is you're both
hurting, Marj.

419
00:26:22,933 --> 00:26:25,633
You're both carrying resentment.

420
00:26:25,767 --> 00:26:30,133
Sometimes in a relationship,
someone has to understand.

421
00:26:30,267 --> 00:26:35,033
Not to lose,
but to make things work.

422
00:26:35,167 --> 00:26:39,000
I'm not like your wife,
who can dismiss you.

423
00:26:39,133 --> 00:26:42,700
You know I'm nothing like her.

424
00:26:44,667 --> 00:26:46,600
Maybe you're right, Mom.

425
00:26:46,733 --> 00:26:48,133
I made mistakes.

426
00:26:48,267 --> 00:26:49,833
I don't want Jasmine
to go through

427
00:26:49,967 --> 00:26:51,600
what I went through.

428
00:26:51,733 --> 00:26:53,333
Watching a family fall apart.

429
00:26:53,467 --> 00:26:54,967
I'll fix this.

430
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:58,267
Maybe it's better to just stop
if we're both done with it.

431
00:26:58,967 --> 00:27:00,233
You know what?

432
00:27:00,367 --> 00:27:03,967
Why end something good?
